HEADWORD: Subaction
<hw>Sub*ac"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. L.
<ets>subactio</ets> a working up, discipline.]</ety> <def>The act of
reducing to any state, as of mixing two bodies completely.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
